coverage_explanation:
The axioms capture the four primary discriminating criteria for CN 2204 22 93:
(1) wine of fresh grapes with no PDO, no PGI, no variety, no vintage designation — modelled via NoPDONoPGINoVarietyNoVintageWineQuality;
(2) presented in a medium container (> 2 L and ≤ 10 L) — modelled via MediumContainer2To10L;
(3) not a semi-sparkling wine — modelled via complement on SemiSparklingWineQuality;
(4) characterised by total dry extract — modelled via TotalDryExtractQuality (reflecting the legal note's reference to Additional Notes 4 and 5 of Chapter 22, which classify wines in this group by their total dry extract content).

Coverage gap (~28%): The legal note for codes 22042222–22042298 references Additional Notes 4 and 5 of Chapter 22, which establish numeric thresholds on total dry extract (g/l) that further sub-divide the codes 22042222, 22042232, 22042243, 22042262, 22042293 etc. The specific dry-extract range that distinguishes 22042293 from sibling codes (e.g. 22042262, 22042282) cannot be fully captured as a numeric decimalRange restriction without introducing a dedicated data property for dry extract concentration (g/l). No such property exists in the current TBox, and no specific numeric threshold for this exact code is stated in the provided note text. The TotalDryExtractQuality class is used to signal the relevance of this criterion, but the actual numeric boundary is not encoded. Additionally, the 'other' residual nature of 22042293 (catching all remaining dry-extract categories not covered by sibling codes) is noted in coverage_explanation but cannot be fully axiomatised without the full Additional Note 4 text.
